1. Examine the cable for any visible signs of bending, suchas a kink or a bend in the cable.

3. Check for any cracks in the outer sheathing or insulation. This can indicate that the cable has been damaged.
4. Look at the ends of the cable to see if any wires are missing. If so, the cable is likely defective, as missing wires can cause problems when connecting the cable with other devices.
